 - row_psum[r1][c+1])\n            # actually top row zeros in c1+1..c2-1 = (c2-c1-1) - (row_sum(r1, c1+1, c2-1))\n            \n            # Let me define:\n            # For col c (0-indexed):\n            # lc(c) = inner_rows - (col_psum[r2][c] - col_psum[r1+1][c])  # zeros in left col\n            # For top row, ones in 0..c: row_psum[r1][c+1]\n            # int ones in inner rows, cols 0..c: psum2d[r2][c+1] - psum2d[r1+1][c+1]\n            \n            # Cost for (c1, c2):\n            # lc(c1) + lc(c2) \n            # + (c2-c1-1) - (row_psum[r1][c2] - row_psum[r1][c1+1])  [top zeros]\n            # + (c2-c1-1) - (row_psum[r2][c2] - row_psum[r2][c1+1])  [bot zeros]\n            # + rect ones interior\n            \n            # rect ones = psum2d[r2][c2] - psum2d[r1+1][c2] - psum2d[r2][c1+1] + psum2d[r1+1][c1+1]\n            \n            # Rearranging, fix c2, minimize over c1 <= c2-3:\n            # terms depending on c1:\n            # lc(c1) - (c2-c1-1) [from -c1 in (c2-c1-1)*2] wait let me be careful\n            \n            # Total cost = lc(c1) + lc(c2)\n            #   + (c2-c1-1) - row_psum[r1][c2] + row_psum[r1][c1+1]\n            #   + (c2-c1-1) - row_psum[r2][c2] + row_psum[r2][c1+1]\n            #   + psum2d[r2][c2] - psum2d[r1+1][c2] - psum2d[r2][c1+1] + psum2d[r1+1][c1+1]\n            \n            # = lc(c2) - row_psum[r1][c2] - row_psum[r2][c2] + psum2d[r2][c2] - psum2d[r1+1][c2]\n            #   + 2*(c2-1)   [from 2*(c2-c1-1) = 2*c2 - 2*c1 - 2, c2 part]\n            #   + lc(c1) + 2*c1 [wait, -2*(c1) from -2*(c2-c1-1)... let me redo]\n            \n            # 2*(c2-c1-1) = 2*c2 - 2*c1 - 2\n            # So c1 part: lc(c1) - 2*c1 + row_psum[r1][c1+1] + row_psum[r2][c1+1] - psum2d[r2][c1+1] + psum2d[r1+1][c1+1]\n            # c2 part: lc(c2) + 2*c2 - 2 - row_psum[r1][c2] - row_psum[r2][c2] + psum2d[r2][c2] - psum2d[r1+1][c2]\n            \n            min_c1 = float('inf')\n            \n            for c2 in range(3, m):\n              